Description: Rim and handle sherd of Corinthian, possibly black-figured, pottery globular aryballos; very worn; on top of rim band of verticals between bands; on edge of rim, diamond pattern; two verticals on outside of handle, glazed below.
Bibliographic references: Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p. 218, no. 9)
Venit 1982 / Painted Pottery from the Greek Mainland found in Egypt, 640-450 BC (p.59, no. A27)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GB.298) (phase 3)
